In ATAG (2018) the impact of aviation is also analyzed by regions: Africa, Asia and Pacific, Europe, Latin America and Caribbean, Middle East and North America. Table 4
reports the rescaled
8 data for the EU27 for which the impact of aviation on GDP is about 4.1% and the total number of jobs amounts to 3.3%, according to the latest statistics. Considering only flights from EU27 to EU27 countries (see Fig. 6
), it turns out that these very rough figures are comparable to those reported in JRC-Unit-B5 (2020): in the first Quarter of 2020, the Observed travel ban impacts 0.02% of the EU27 GDP and 0.13% under the EUROC scenario, while in the worst scenario (EUROC-L) the global impact can go up to 1.98% on a yearly base. In terms of job losses, in the first Quarter of 2020, the Observed and EUROC scenario report 40,000 and 330,000 job losses respectively. For the whole 2020, under the worst scenario (EUROC-L) this number rises to 5 million of job losses. Looking at Fig. 6, Fig. 7
it emerges that the Observed scenario has different shape locally and globally at EU27 level.(see Table 5, Table 6
)
